column5: 13C up here and rain on and off all morning. Flash freeze tonight to -21. Should make her nice and slick out on the ice.....

+ 11 here in Lindsay but the sun is shining, windy though, gusts to about 60 km/h. If I had known we weren't going to get all the rain they were calling for I'd have gone fishing again today. Going to try to squeeze in a day later in the week if I can, got to get me one of those whities.
....I was out with the puppy today scouting a few local ice holes and she was very slick!  Cleats will be in order tomorrow if I decide to get up and get out.
12*C at downtown TO, should've check out the lake front ice conditions.
I was out on GB today going for Lakers and Whities.....there was lots of snow when we arrived at 0800....when we left at 1200, there was none at all, it was all SLUSH!! No sign of snow anywhere!!
Like 63 F here today and an ice storm warning out for tonight and tomorrow, tomorrows high like 33f. I will be a bad day for driving.
Mild here now Wayne more freezing rain coming wednesday morning and then more snow 15cms. come saturday more snow .  No signs of spring here
Dangerous conditions out there right now, be careful going to work today folks.....and if you're lucky enough to be heading out fishing, be careful not to slip and breat the camera  Maureen
